A good answer includes endpoints like:
- POST /v1/embeddings {model_id, inputs:[...], input_type, tenant_id} -> {embeddings:[...], model_version, usage}
- POST /v1/indexes/{index_id}/upsert {index_version, documents:[{doc_id, text|chunks, metadata, embedding?}], embed_model_id?} -> {upserted, failed[]}
- POST /v1/indexes/{index_id}/query {index_version, query_text|query_embedding, top_k, filters, return_fields, citation_mode} -> {results:[{doc_id, chunk_id, score, metadata, snippet, citation}], trace_id}
- GET /v1/models and GET /v1/indexes/{index_id}/versions
Include: idempotency keys for upsert, trace_id for observability, explicit version fields, and stable error codes (429 rate limit, 400 validation, 503 dependency).

Non-functional requirements to clarify: latency SLOs for embed/query, availability and multi-region needs, data privacy/tenant isolation, throughput/QPS and burstiness, cost constraints, maximum document size, retention/deletion, and consistency requirements for newly upserted docs (read-after-write).
